with Google Anlaytics, Ahrefs / SEMRush and other content performance tools.\n\nTo learn more about who we are, our culture, and whether Taskade is the right place for you, please contact john@taskade.com"},{"title":"Copywriter","location":"San Francisco / Singapore / Remote","apply_url":"mailto:john@taskade.com","content":"[Taskade](https://www.taskade.com) is building a real-time organization and collaboration tool for distributed teams. We reimagining the future of work, remote collaboration, and team productivity. Our mission is simple, to help teams get work done, faster and smarter, in one unified workspace.\n\nAt Taskade, youll have the chance to work with a small, closely-knit team and make a big impact on our product, business, and engineering efforts.\n\n## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n* We are looking for a highly motivated writer to help us create content across multiple channels for Taskade related to productivity, remote work, and more.\n* Work directly with the head of marketing.\n* Publish directly to Taskade's blog and templates gallery.\n* Follow content guideline for Taskade.\n\nWe value T-shaped people. That is, people who are both generalists (highly skilled at a broad set of valuable thingsthe top of the T) and also experts (among the best in their field within a narrow disciplinethe vertical leg of the T). An expert who is too narrow has difficulty collaborating. A generalist who doesnt go deep enough in a single area ends up on the margins, not really contributing as an individual.\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n* Strong communication skills, ability to articulate complex ideas.\n* Native-level command of the English language.\n* Over 4 years of experience writing high-impact content.\n* Experience publishing to Wordpress, Zendesk, and various CMS.\n* Deep understanding and passion for team productivity and collaboration tools.\n* (Bonus) Familiarity with Google Anlaytics, Ahrefs / SEMRush and other content performance tools.\n\nTo learn more about who we are, our culture, and whether Taskade is the right place for you, please contact john@taskade.com"},{"title":"Front-end Engineer","location":"San Francisco / Singapore / Remote","apply_url":"mailto:john@taskade.com","content":"[Taskade](https://www.taskade.com) is building a real-time organization and collaboration tool for distributed teams. We reimagining the future of work, remote collaboration, and team productivity. Our mission is simple, to help teams get work done, faster and smarter, in one unified workspace.\n\nAt Taskade, youll have the chance to work with a small, closely-knit team and make a big impact on our product, business, and engineering efforts.\n\n## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n* We are looking for skilled front-end engineers with a deep understanding of user interface and design. Were a small team, and in order for us to thrive, we need members who have the drive and ability to work on a wide array of products.\n* From working on our landing pages, templates showcase, to the user on-boarding experience, youll get the chance to experience a wide variety of development scenarios.\n\nWe value T-shaped people. That is, people who are both generalists (highly skilled at a broad set of valuable thingsthe top of the T) and also experts (among the best in their field within a narrow disciplinethe vertical leg of the T). An expert who is too narrow has difficulty collaborating. A generalist who doesnt go deep enough in a single area ends up on the margins, not really contributing as an individual.\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n* Experience with JavaScript.\n* Experience with React, Typescript, and Redux.\n* Deep understanding of cloud architecture and application deployment.\n* Be deeply interested in the long-term view. Yes, we need to deliver value rapidly, but our problem domain will grow dramatically over time. Figure out where we need to be in a year and identify how we'll get there incrementally, while helping us manage and constrain technical debt and other forms of unnecessary complications which will in the long-run serve us poorly.\n* To be a quick learner. Were looking for software engineers who thrive on learning new technologies. As a startup, and we have a lot of problem domains that need to be worked on, and you should have the ability and drive to adapt accordingly.\n* Versatility. You understand how all the pieces fit together (front-end, database, network layer, etc.) and how they impact the performance of your application.\n\nTo learn more about who we are, our culture, and whether Taskade is the right place for you, please contact john@taskade.com"},{"title":"Full Stack Engineer","location":"San Francisco / Singapore / Remote","apply_url":"mailto:john@taskade.com","content":"[Taskade](https://www.taskade.com) is building a real-time organization and collaboration tool for distributed teams. We reimagining the future of work, remote collaboration, and team productivity. Our mission is simple, to help teams get work done, faster and smarter, in one unified workspace.\n\nAt Taskade, youll have the chance to work with a small, closely-knit team and make a big impact on our product, business, and engineering efforts.\n\n## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n* We are looking for skilled full-stack engineers to help us work through tough, multifaceted problems. Were a small team, and in order for us to thrive we need members who have the drive and ability to work on a wide array of products.\n* From developing our data pipeline, to working on the APIs that power our website and mobile app, youll get the chance to experience a wide variety of development scenarios.\n* Real-time data is core to our business, and as we grow well need our backend to be ready to scale with us. Ensuring every service we release is ready to scale is key to our growth strategy.\n\nWe value T-shaped people. That is, people who are both generalists (highly skilled at a broad set of valuable thingsthe top of the T) and also experts (among the best in their field within a narrow disciplinethe vertical leg of the T). An expert who is too narrow has difficulty collaborating. A generalist who doesnt go deep enough in a single area ends up on the margins, not really contributing as an individual.\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n* Experience with JavaScript.\n* Experience with React, Typescript and Redux.\n* Experience with RDBMS. (PostgreSQL preferred)\n* Experience with real-time data and back-end technologies. (e.g. Redis.)\n* Experience working with WebSocket. (e.g. Socket.IO)\n* Experience designing and developing integration solutions using Web Services. (RESTful APIs/GraphQL)\n* Deep understanding of cloud architecture and application deployment.\n* Be deeply interested in the long-term view. Yes, we need to deliver value rapidly, but our problem domain will grow dramatically over time. Figure out where we need to be in a year and identify how we'll get there incrementally, while helping us manage and constrain technical debt and other forms of unnecessary complications which will in the long run serve us poorly.\n* To be a quick learner. Were looking for software engineers who thrive on learning new technologies. As a startup, and we have a lot of problem domains that need to be worked on, and you should have the ability and drive to adapt accordingly.\n* Versatility. You understand how all the pieces fit together (front-end, database, network layer, etc.) and how they impact the performance of your application.\n\nTo learn more about who we are, our culture, and whether Taskade is the right place for you, please contact john@taskade.com"},{"title":"Product Designer","location":"San Francisco / Singapore / Remote","apply_url":"mailto:john@taskade.com","content":"[Taskade](https://www.taskade.com) is building a real-time organization and collaboration tool for distributed teams. We reimagining the future of work, remote collaboration, and team productivity. Our mission is simple, to help teams get work done, faster and smarter, in one unified workspace.\n\nAt Taskade, youll have the chance to work with a small, closely-knit team and make a big impact on our product, business, and engineering efforts.\n\n## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n* We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Product / UI / UX Designer who is passionate about creating practical, friendly and human solutions to complex problems. They will be joining the core team to help build the future of productivity.\n* Work directly with head of product and engineering leads.\n* UI/UX mockups of new features.\n* Design for the web, mobile web, mobile and desktop.\n* Help create a coherent design language for the product.\n* Create assets, sprites, graphics.\n* Interview customers to gather feedback.\n\nWe value T-shaped people. That is, people who are both generalists (highly skilled at a broad set of valuable thingsthe top of the T) and also experts (among the best in their field within a narrow disciplinethe vertical leg of the T). An expert who is too narrow has difficulty collaborating. A generalist who doesnt go deep enough in a single area ends up on the margins, not really contributing as an individual.\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n* Strong communication skills, ability to articulate complex ideas.\n* Over 4 years of experience designing products.\n* Experience with Figma, Illustrator, Photoshop, Framer and equivalent tools.\n* Deep understanding and passion for team productivity and collaboration tools.\n* (Bonus) HTML/CSS/JS, React, NextJS.\n\nTo learn more about who we are, our culture, and whether Taskade is the right place for you, please contact john@taskade.com"},{"title":"Product Growth","location":"San Francisco / Singapore / Remote","apply_url":"mailto:john@taskade.com","content":"[Taskade](https://www.taskade.com) is building a real-time organization and collaboration tool for distributed teams. We reimagining the future of work, remote collaboration, and team productivity. Our mission is simple, to help teams get work done, faster and smarter, in one unified workspace.\n\nAt Taskade, youll have the chance to work with a small, closely-knit team and make a big impact on our product, business, and engineering efforts.\n\n## RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n* Develop messaging and go-to-market strategies for new products, plans, and audiences.\n* Partner closely with product management and product teams to craft a repeatable playbook for feature releases.\n* Create high-quality marketing material with a team of talented designers and developers  this includes landing pages, marketing videos, product tutorials, webinars, and more.\n* Help create a coherent marketing guideline for Taskade.\n* Become an expert on our product, market, competitors, and customers.\n\nWe value T-shaped people. That is, people who are both generalists (highly skilled at a broad set of valuable thingsthe top of the T) and also experts (among the best in their field within a narrow disciplinethe vertical leg of the T). An expert who is too narrow has difficulty collaborating. A generalist who doesnt go deep enough in a single area ends up on the margins, not really contributing as an individual.\n\n## REQUIREMENTS\n\n* Strong communication skills, ability to articulate complex ideas.\n* Over 4 years of experience leading high-performance growth / marketing teams.\n* A stickler for details, who can work with the team to ensure product positioning and messaging is consistent across every touchpoint.\n* Deep understanding and passion for team productivity and collaboration tools.\n* Familiarity with Google Anlaytics, Ahrefs, SEMRush and other content performance tools.\n* Someone who appreciates a deep dive into the data, but understands how to blend metrics, best practices, and intuition.\n\nTo learn more about who we are, our culture, and whether Taskade is the right place for you, please contact john@taskade.com"}],"comparisons":[{"competitor_name":"Airtable","slug":"free-airtable-alternative","excerpt":"Taskade is the best free alternative to Airtable.","content":"## What is Airtable?\n\n### The company history\n\nAirtable is a spreadsheet-like app that lets you create and share tables with team members and clients. It was originally founded in 2012 by CEO and founder, Howie Liu, who wanted to solve the problem of information overload in an office setting. The digital landscape has changed a lot since then. With more and more people working remotely and managing their business on the go, Airtable has evolved to meet these new needs.\n\nAirtable is a web-based spreadsheet program where you can create, modify and share your tables with others. With Airtable, you have the power to build complex databases without being an expert. You can build a database in minutes that lists all of your customers or has a list of how many people attended each event you hosted.","jumbotron_title":"An Airtable Alternative","jumbotron_subtitle":"Looking for an alternative to Airtable? Meet Taskade","competitor_price":"Paid","taskade_price":"Free","logo":"static_images/comparisons/airtable.png","feature_sections":[{"features":[{"name":"The Visual Playground","tooltip_text":"Availability of templates and their ease of use.","competitor_offering":"Develop database orientated templates","taskade_offering":"Develop customizable templates"},{"name":"Own Your Workspace","taskade_offering":"Fully customizable workspace and progress tracking","tooltip_text":"The ability to custom tailor your workspace and project structure to how you like it. ","competitor_offering":"Customizability is restricted to tables and databases"},{"taskade_offering":"Adaptable data visualization","competitor_offering":"Data is incompatible with certain views offered","name":"Consistency Is Simplicity","tooltip_text":"The ease of how data is translated across different platforms and view modes (Eg, List, Mindmap, Action board)."}],"section_title":"Design Freedom"},{"features":[{"name":"Let's Talk ","competitor_offering":"Comment syncing, no live vi